law.text:
As used in this chapter, unless the context requires otherwise:
"Commissioner" means the Commissioner of Agriculture;
"Department" means the Department of Agriculture;
"Grower" means a bona fide producer of tobacco, either by himself or by tenant, sharecropper or hired person;
"Warehouse" means any tobacco warehouse operating as a place of sale for tobacco in this state; and
"Warehouseman" means the owner, operator, manager, lessee or proprietor of a warehouse engaged in selling tobacco or his agents or employees.
